Text: So, condoms breaking isn’t a typical thing. I mean it CAN and DOES happen from time to time but it’s pretty rare if you use them right. If a condom does break, it’s probably because it’s been put on wrong, has dried out, or gets torn from nails or anything else sharp. If it broke, you can usually tell either by feeling it or seeing it once your man pulls out. If you’re nervous or unsure, you can always take the morning after pill.
